\section{Matrices for random effects}
\label{sec:matr-rand-effects}

The matrices involved in the random effects can be obtained with

@ 
<<>>=
shoe3 <- subset(shoe.b, boy<=5)
lmm1  <- lmer( wear ~ mat + (1|boyf), data=shoe3 )
SG    <- LMM_Sigma_G( lmm1 )
@ %def 

@ 
<<>>=
round( SG$Sigma*10 )
@ %def 

@ 
<<>>=
SG$G
@ %def 





